de.affect.emotion

Class EmotionVector

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.affect.emotion.EmotionVector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<Emotion>

    public class EmotionVector
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<Emotion>
    This class holds a collection of emotions for a predefined set of emotion types. It contains exactly one Emotion instance for each emotion type.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Patrick Gebhard (based on the work of Micheal Kipp and Martin Klesen)

    • Constructor Detail

      • EmotionVector

        public EmotionVector(Personality personality,
             Mood mood,
             java.util.List emotionTypes)
        Creates a new EmotionVector for the specified emotion types
        The initial intensity of the emotions in this collection is the same as the baseline. The baseline is computed based on the emotion type and the character's personality.
        Parameters:
        personality - a personality object
        emotionTypes - the predefined set of emotion types
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if one of the arguments is null or if the list of emotion types is empty

      • add

        public boolean add(Emotion emotion)
        Adds the specified emotion to the collection of emotions if its type is one of the predefined emotion types. The new emotion replaces the emotion with the same type. The method returns true if the emotion is added to the collection and false otherwise.
        Parameters:
        emotion - the new emotion
        Returns:
        true if the emotion is added to the collection and false otherwise.
        See Also:
        getEmotionTypes()

        public boolean hasType(EmotionType type)

        Returns:

      • merge

        public void merge(EmotionVector newEmotions)
        Merges a EmotionVector object with the current EmotionVector object. In the case both vectors store the equal emotion(s), the old emotion(s) will be replaced by the new emotion(s). Otherwise, the new emotion(s) will be added to the collection.
        Parameters:
        newEmotions - an emotion vector
